  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">John Murray Spear writes: &quot;Pleas pay to Rob&apos;t F. Wallcut, Ag&apos;t of Lib[erato]r two &amp; 42/100 dollars rec&apos;d by R. D. Webb from James Haughton for Prisoners&apos; Friend, &amp; by him (R. D. Webb) expended for the benefit of the Anti Slavery bazaar, as stated in his ap(?) rendered.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The postscript consists of a separate note signed by Maria Weston Chapman, asking F[rancis] Jackson to &quot;pray pay the above-named sum&quot; to R. F. Wallcut from the funds from the fair.</subfield>
